body:
> I think it just parses everything in vendor before looking into your code?

@AlexP11223 It's a bit more complex. Psalm tracks what files were included during autoload registration (e.g. those in `autoload.files` entries of installed packages) and parses them, those referenced by them and so on.

@simonberger thanks for the reproducer.

@weirdan that would work great, would it also be possible to add a config option to scope files to minimum PHP versions? 

There are definitely other different ways of doing this, such as:

```
$version = phpversion();
$version = PHP_MAJOR_VERSION . PHP_MINOR_VERSION;
```
